# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Velora Agroprocessing Ltd. static HTML website.

## What Was Implemented

### Documentation Review
- Fetched the latest Vercel Web Analytics documentation from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
- Verified the correct implementation method for static HTML websites
- Confirmed that static HTML sites use the CDN script approach and do not require the `@vercel/analytics` npm package

### Changes Made

#### Modified Files (9 HTML files):
1. **index.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to homepage
2. **about.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to about page
3. **careers.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to careers page
4. **contact.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to contact page
5. **distribution.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to distribution page
6. **impact.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to impact page
7. **investors.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to investors page
8. **news.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to news page
9. **products.html** - Added Vercel Analytics script to products page

### Implementation Details

**Script Added:**
```html
<script defer src="https://cdn.vercel-insights.com/v1/script.js"></script>
```

**Placement:**
- The script was placed in the `<head>` section of each HTML file, just before the closing `</head>` tag
- Used the `defer` attribute to ensure the script loads asynchronously without blocking page rendering
- Positioned after all CSS links to maintain proper loading order

### Technical Approach

Since this is a **static HTML website** (not a JavaScript framework like Next.js, React, or Vue):
- No npm package installation was required
- No build process modifications were needed
- No package.json or lock files to update
- Used the CDN-based script injection method as recommended by Vercel's official documentation

The CDN script automatically:
- Tracks page views across all HTML pages
- Collects Web Vitals metrics (LCP, FID, CLS, etc.)
- Sends analytics data to Vercel when the site is deployed on Vercel's platform
- Works without any additional configuration

### Verification

✅ All 9 HTML files successfully updated with analytics script
✅ HTML structure remains valid with proper syntax
✅ Script placement follows Vercel's best practices
✅ No breaking changes to existing functionality
✅ Analytics will be active once deployed to Vercel

### Next Steps for Site Owner

1. **Deploy to Vercel:** Push these changes to your repository
2. **Enable Analytics:** In the Vercel dashboard, go to your project's Analytics section and click "Enable"
3. **View Data:** After deployment, analytics data will start appearing in the Vercel dashboard

### Notes

- The analytics script uses the `defer` attribute for optimal performance
- The script is loaded from Vercel's CDN and will only activate when deployed on Vercel
- No changes were needed to JavaScript (script.js) or CSS (style.css) files
- The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation as of July 2026
- All existing website functionality remains intact
